column2: We have had 7+ inches of rain the past two weeks.
Four inches of rain on Wednesday and Thursday of this week.
Secchi disc almost hit the bottom.  The spot I have been taking readings is at 7.5 feet.
Most of the ice went out Wednesday 3/25/87.
Sunny with light winds from the northeast.
Cold and drizzly last week.  Hot and humid with occasional heavy rains this week- heavy weed growth this year.
Sprayed diquat on the weeds on June 2nd.
A large amount of chuckweed on the lake.
Weather has been hot- humid and very little rain.
About an inch of rain since last reading.
Sky became overcast while out taking the reading.
About 14" of ice.  Oxygen level is 10.6.  Monitored with Dwight l. Louison.
No algae but excessive weeds- one inch of rain on 6/28- only rain to amount to anything this summer.  Oxygen level is 6.4. monitored with Dwight l. Louison.
The water is about 3' below normal.  5" of rain from 8/1-8/30.  Monitored with Tony Habeck.
Rain gauge reading from 8/2-8/9 is 1.2 inches.
Rain gauge reading from 8/9-8/16 is 0.1 inches.
Weeds harvested starting 8/16 to 8/18.  Rain gauge reading from 8/15-8/29 is 0.7 inches.
Rain gauge reading from 8/27-10/11 is 7.5 inches.
More of a problem with duck week rather than algae.
Had a major runoff from some area.  Area that was suspected was said to have proper erosion control.  Feel this happened after the rain that clouded the lake.
Enjoyment impaired because of aquatic plants.  Harvesting to begin June 30- 1997.
Cloudy- moderate breeze - Water 58. Starting turnover.
In the middle of turnover- moderate breeze- overcast.
Lake had terrible rain + runoff 4/8 just recovering now- water is quite turbid. Minimal depth clarity- first reading. Ordered dissolved oxygen meter 4/19.
Water quite choppy- in middle of cold front lake is still very murky.
Very windy- considerable chop from East.
Water had chop- lots of dead vegetation floating water somewhat turbid.
Lake had slight chop. Was seen to be a little more murky than last week probably due to chemical treatment of curly leaf last Tuesday. Treated 30 acres.
Quite windy- lots of floating debris in water decaying plants etc. Water otherwise appears to be clearing up a bit.

column1: Very calm  + clear sunshine. Water quality is very good visibility is the best it's been this early in the year.

column2: Had rain visibilty down slightly- water level up somewhat. Moderate chop on the lake.
Water had moderate chop appears to be clearing up from rains.
It was late in the evening but lake was calm + last of a sunny day. Lake is really getting depleted of oxygen.
Water apepared as clear but did not get normal depth perhaps due to taking reading so early. Water calm- weather clear.
Lake was quite calm visibilty a little worse- some bloom. Lake was quite calm visibilty a little worse- some bloom.
Water Had a slight chop + continues murky.
Slight Chop on water- surface looked a little clearer.
Slight chop on water- water at shore looks as though it's starting to clear. Water when placing Secchi down looks worse.
Water was quite murky- an obvious algae bloom + some aquatics are dying or dropping down anyway- Slight chop on water.
Water is still very turbid. Slight chop on the lake- alot of the weeds have gone down.
Lake was calm- dropped 1st 6" for drawdown since Friday 8/29. Water still very murky.
Drawdown has begun as of 8/29 down 19 1/4". Light chop on water- still murky.
Just started refilling the lake today. Will be two weeks before Secchi's + dissolved oxygen can be taken.
Call + Clear. Water starting to get murky. Curly leaf may be starting to die.
Very calm + clear. Water a little murky- curly leaf pondweed still around. Overabundance of sago pondweed.
Water was choppy curly leaf starting to die.
Water was calm- algae bloom started.
Lake was choppy- appeared more clear- bloom pretty much gone.
Water was calm but quite murky.
Lake relatively calm water reasonably clear.
Very calm water quality affected by some algae.
Lake had considerable chop + perhaps a little more cloudiness due to treatment 4/19.
Slight chop on lake- appears a little clearer. Mostly cloudy 55.
Water looks to be clearing up more slight chop.
Slight chop algae blooming- water quite clear.
Water clear lots of bloom- very choppy.
Just a slight chop new algae showing otherwise very clear + good.
Light chop visibility improving but considerable new algae. Baby bass in swarms.
A little choppy but clarity is great more new algae growth. Bottom DO was incorrect due to a problem with the meter.
Cloudy with chop- clarity good very low oxygen at bottom.
Slight Chop - Duck Weed has sure started to bloom.
Water Calm - Still a ton of duckweed. Water has cleared up some. DO was incorrect due to problem with meter.
Slight chop water has cleared up discovered previous readings of DO wrong.
Water moderate chop- lake weeds improving duck weed deminishing.
Fairly calm water on browner side. Readings this summer for DO were incorrect due to problem with meter. Readings were not taken in Sept + Oct because lake was drawn down for rebuild of landing.
Very cloudy + misting- slight chop. Last reading before ice. Will take readings this winter.
Lake was very choppy + murky from rains.
Lake was calm but tanic stained- otherwuse quality quite good.
Lake was choppy- water appeared less tanic.
Calm + foggy water looks pretty clear.
Lake was very calm + skies were clear. Water quality looked visually improved.
Overcast + moderate chop. Lake quite murky.
Water very muddy due to heavy rain. Heavy chop due to windy condition-
Slight chop- lake dropped about 20" to date. Water quite clear. Will not be able to do D.O. at 9 ft. through the summer due to water level drop. Just a slit chop on lake.
Water somewhat murky- lake calm. Water level down 3 ft.
Lake calm- fish dieoff- approx. 1000 80% bluegills. Larger fish were primarily suckers- 25% northerns- some bass + several jumbp perch.
Some what choppy- no more dieoff of fish. visability improved somewhat.
Good chop- water quality moving up.
Walm calm + overcast. lots of duckweed.
Lake calm- alot of duckweed on top.
Temp 82 degrees- partly cloudy- weed harvester lanes made navigation much easier than in July.
